				<p><em>(Why the most dangerous thing in your life doesn't look dangerous at all.)</em></p>
				
				<h2>Not all monsters look like monsters</h2>
				<p>There are monsters you recognise immediately, the kind the body understands without needing interpretation. They come with claws or teeth or madness in the eyes, they move without manners, and they announce themselves as enemies. But the thing that quietly ruins most human lives does not arrive like that. It does not arrive as terror. It does not arrive as danger. It does not arrive as something the system instinctively rejects.</p>
				
